{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Fresh & Delish","author":"Kim"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3feffddb-6ee6-56ac-830c-603029d7efd1","excerpt":"DOES NOT CONTAIN FROG This snack idea is so simple I almost didn’t post it; doing so feels a bit like writing a recipe for a cup of tea…","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-51304.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 107.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"chia goup\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-ae3ac.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-5d159.jpg 148w,\n/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-35ab3.jpg 295w,\n/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-ae3ac.jpg 590w,\n/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-12342.jpg 885w,\n/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-51304.jpg 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><strong>DOES NOT CONTAIN FROG</strong></p>\n<p>This snack idea is so simple I almost didn’t post it; doing so feels a bit like writing a recipe for a cup of tea. However, I’ve had at least five people ask me about this concoction in the space of a week so here it is.</p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>I particularly like chia prepared this way because it’s an energy source that’s light enough that I can drink it then proceed to exercise 15 minutes later without feeling remotely ill – even if that exercise is teaching Body Attack with it’s tuck-jump-burpees. There are not many foods for which I can say the same.</p>\n<p>Now for the credits: idea courtesy of my sister, and the name… inspired by my mother who came close to convincing her squad of swimmers, using post-exercise nutritional arguments, that she was in fact drinking frogs eggs!</p>\n<p>Serves 1</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 tablespoons chia seeds (any colour)</li>\n<li>juice of half a lemon or lime (if you like stronger citrus flavours, add juice from the whole fruit)</li>\n<li>300mL water</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Combine all ingredients in a jar. Secure lid and shake well. Shake a couple of times over the next 5-10 minutes so the chia doesn’t clump together too densely. Refrigerate or allow to sit for at least 30 minutes and you’re done.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Citrus chia ‘frogs eggs’","date":"August 23, 2014","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1000,"height":1074,"src":"/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-3238c.jpg","srcSet":"/static/chia-goup-f06e50fa1ca8a98532892e0fb7d78a7c-3238c.jpg 1x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2014/08/23/2014-7-27-citrus-chia-frogs-eggs/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014/08/16/2014-7-27-stuffed-capsicums-with-parsley-pesto/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Stuffed capsicums with parsley pesto","tags":["Appetisers","Dairy/lactose-free friendly","Nut-free friendly","Sides","Vegan friendly","Vegetarian"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014/12/07/2014-7-27-honey-roasted-carrot-chestnut-and-silverbeet-salad/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Honey-roasted carrot, chestnut and silverbeet salad","tags":["Dairy/lactose-free friendly","Salads","Vegan friendly","Vegetarian"]}}}}